div.div: Ganta is the only survivor after a mysterious man in red slaughters a classroom full of teenagers. He's framed for the carnage, sentenced to die, and locked away in the most twisted prison ever built: Deadman Wonderland. And then it gets worse. At Deadman Wonderland, convicts are forced into brutal deathmatches for the amusement of the masses, the cheers of the crowd drowning out the screams of the dismembered. Even when Ganta befriends Shiro, an unusual female inmate, his dark fate crushes all hope —until he discovers the strange ability to wield his spilled blood as a weapon. Ganta learns his new skill might be related to the murderous man in red and uncovers disturbing secrets that could expose those who stole his freedom. He's determined to see justice served —but first he'll have to fight for his life in a prison that holds a million ways to die. (Source: FUNimation)

Unable to hear, speak, or wield a sword, Prince Bojji doesnt seem like a typical heir to the throneand his kingdom agrees. But his fateful encounter with Kage, a shadow on the ground, gives him his first true friend. The two set off on a grand adventure and, together, form a bond that can overcome any obstacle...even being king.
(Source: Funimation)

He and she were enemies. Until he knew he had the same loneliness in a dichotomized world. They are cheap, strong, and never die. The ultimate life regeneration system "Arcadia" was born from teenage soldiers who fight by making full use of the complex regeneration <Respawn>. They were invincible boys and girls (children who transcended death) who died on the battlefield and revived. The forefront of the war in which the two great powers compete for hegemony. Akihito, a boy who leads a platoon as an ace of the United States Army, is ordered to collect confidential information that is inevitable to be wiped out because of his poor performance. However, Akihito, who has kept his companions in an unexpected battle and collapse, is isolated deep underground where complex regeneration <respawn> is impossible, along with his fateful nemesis, the elite girl Philia of the Federal Army. Two people who have opposite personalities and skills and have the worst compatibility will cooperate and aim to return to the ground. The story of the encounter and resonance between him and her who continued to die on the battlefield that never died begins!

100-nichi Go ni Shinu Akuyaku Reijou wa Mainichi ga Totemo Tanoshii.

"You will die in 100 days." Duchess Lelouche received the prophesy from God. Her fianc, the Crown Prince, has been distracted by other women and is said to be on the verge of breaking off their engagement... And even if Lelouche knew the future, she still couldn't change the fact that she was going to die. But she can change the way she dies, and the effects of her death - or so she was told. So she made a bet with God.
"If I may die beautifully, please reward me." "If you do good. I will give you whatever you want in your next life." Now Lelouche will act to support the family she is leaving behind, and fight the "conspiracy" that will lead to her eventual death...
(Source: SB Creative, translated)
